    "eyebrow": "Settlement Patterns",
    "num": "04",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">04</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Settlement Patterns</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Where Did Texicans Settle?</h2><ul><li>Primarily in Mexican Texas along rivers and fertile land</li><li>Settlements encouraged by Mexican land grant system</li><li>Empresarios facilitated Anglo and Mexican settlement</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans settled in areas granted by Mexican authorities, often near rivers for agriculture, with empresarios acting as land agents to attract settlers (s7, s8). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Stephen F. Austin’s colony was a major empresario settlement attracting both Anglo and Mexican settlers.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Map key Texican settlements and discuss why location mattered.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texicans only lived in urban centers or ignoring Mexican land policies.</p></div></div>",
