    "eyebrow": "Settlement Challenges",
    "num": "06",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">06</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Settlement Challenges</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Interactions with Native American Tribes</h2><ul><li>Texicans faced conflicts and alliances with local tribes</li><li>Native groups included Comanche, Apache, and others</li><li>Relations influenced security and settlement patterns</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican settlements were often on contested lands, leading to both conflict and negotiation with Native tribes, affecting frontier stability (s7, s9). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Some Texican communities formed trade relations with tribes, while others experienced raids disrupting settlement.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how Native American relations impacted Texican settlement success.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing Native tribes only as adversaries without recognizing complex relations.</p></div></div>",
