    "eyebrow": "Cultural Identity",
    "num": "07",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">07</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Identity</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Blending Mexican and Anglo Cultures</h2><ul><li>Texicans adopted Mexican legal and religious traditions</li><li>Anglo settlers introduced English language and customs</li><li>Resulted in a hybrid Texican identity</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican culture was a fusion of Mexican governance and Anglo settler influences, creating unique social and cultural practices (s2, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican towns held Catholic mass but also elected Anglo-style local officials.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify examples of cultural blending in Texican communities.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming cultural assimilation was one-way or uniform.</p></div></div>",
