    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">08</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Historical Role</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texicans in Early Texas History</h2><ul><li>Key participants in Texas Revolution (1835-1836)</li><li>Negotiated between Mexican authorities and Anglo settlers</li><li>Helped shape Texas’s political future</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans played crucial roles in the political and military events leading to Texas independence, balancing complex loyalties (s2, s15). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican leaders signed the Texas Declaration of Independence alongside Anglo revolutionaries.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss how Texican involvement influenced the revolution’s outcome.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking Texican contributions in favor of Anglo narratives.</p></div></div>",
