      "secnum": "Deep Dive 08",
      "h": "Texican Agency in the Texas Revolution",
      "body": "<p><strong>Why this deserves a deeper look.</strong> Texicans played crucial roles in the political and military events leading to Texas independence, balancing complex loyalties (s2, s15).</p><p><strong>Source boundary.</strong> Teach this point from jinxschwartz.com; tshaonline.org. If a learner asks for a statistic, date, standard, or local procedure that is not in the knowledge base, Bernard and the presenter should mark it as a research gap instead of improvising.</p><h3>What to emphasize</h3><ul><li>Key participants in Texas Revolution (1835-1836)</li><li>Negotiated between Mexican authorities and Anglo settlers</li><li>Helped shape Texas’s political future</li></ul><h3>Worked example</h3><p>Texican leaders signed the Texas Declaration of Independence alongside Anglo revolutionaries.</p><h3>Practice and transfer</h3><p>Discuss how Texican involvement influenced the revolution’s outcome.</p><p><strong>Common mistake to prevent.</strong> Overlooking Texican contributions in favor of Anglo narratives.</p><p class=\"ref\"><strong>Source anchor:</strong> jinxschwartz.com; tshaonline.org <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p>"
