    "num": "09",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">09</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Source Insight</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texas Declaration of Independence and Texicans</h2><ul><li>Texican signatories affirmed independence from Mexico</li><li>Document reflects shared grievances of diverse settlers</li><li>Highlights Texican political engagement</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Texas Declaration of Independence includes Texican leaders, showing their commitment to Texas’s political transformation (s15). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Excerpts reveal Texicans’ concerns about Mexican governance and desire for self-rule.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze a Texican signer’s statement and its significance.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring Texican voices in revolutionary documents.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide9\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best distinguishes a &#39;Texican&#39; from a &#39;Texian&#39;?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;Texicans were Mexican settlers in Texas; Texians were Anglo-American settlers.&quot;,&quot;Texicans were settlers after Texas became a U.S. state; Texians were before.&quot;,&quot;Texicans were Native American tribes; Texians were settlers.&quot;,&quot;Texicans were from Texas; Texians were from Mexico.&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; refers to Mexican settlers in Texas, while &#39;Texian&#39; typically refers to Anglo-American settlers during the Mexican Texas period.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Describe the cultural background of the Texicans and how it influenced their role in early Texas history.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Response should include definition of Texicans as Mexican settlers, mention of blended Mexican and Anglo cultural influences, discussion of settlement patterns, and their political/military role in the Texas Revolution.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Texicans were Mexican settlers in Texas who blended Mexican and Anglo cultures. Their lifestyle on the frontier involved land grants and interaction with Native tribes. They played a key role in early Texas history by participating in the Texas Revolution and shaping the region&#39;s identity.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Texicans were Mexican settlers blending cultures and involved in Texas history&quot;,&quot;Mexican settlers called Texicans who influenced Texas through culture and revolution&quot;,&quot;Texicans had a mixed cultural background and were active in Texas settlement and revolution&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
