    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">10</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Settlement Map</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Tracing Texican Land Grants and Settlements</h2><ul><li>Empresario grants shaped settlement geography</li><li>Key settlements along Brazos and Colorado Rivers</li><li>Mixed Mexican and Anglo populations in colonies</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Mapping empresario land grants helps visualize where Texicans lived and how settlement patterns developed (s7, s8). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Stephen F. Austin’s colony was a major settlement area with diverse inhabitants.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Locate major Texican settlements on a map and discuss geographic advantages.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming settlements were randomly distributed without policy influence.</p></div></div>",
