    "eyebrow": "Political Role",
    "num": "17",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">17</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Political Role</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texicans in the Texas Revolution</h2><ul><li>Texicans played key roles in the fight for independence</li><li>Many Texicans supported breaking from Mexico</li><li>They participated in battles and political assemblies</li><li>Texican leaders helped draft the Texas Declaration of Independence</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans were active participants in the Texas Revolution, contributing militarily and politically to the movement for independence from Mexico. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican leaders like José Antonio Navarro signed the Texas Declaration of Independence in 1836.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss why Texicans might have supported the revolution despite Mexican heritage.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming all Texicans opposed the revolution; some remained loyal to Mexico.</p></div></div>",
