    "num": "18",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">18</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Source Analysis</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Examining the Texas Declaration of Independence</h2><ul><li>Document signed by Texican and Anglo leaders in 1836</li><li>Outlined grievances against Mexican government</li><li>Declared Texas an independent republic</li><li>Reflects Texican political aspirations and identity</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Texas Declaration of Independence is a key primary source revealing Texican and settler motivations for revolution and their vision for Texas. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Analyze a passage expressing complaints about Mexican laws restricting immigration and trade.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify how the Declaration reflects Texican concerns and goals.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing the Declaration as solely Anglo settler document, ignoring Texican signatories.</p></div></div>",
