    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">19</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Settlement Mapping</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Tracing Texican Land Grants and Settlements</h2><ul><li>Empresario grants shaped settlement geography</li><li>Settlements clustered near rivers and trade routes</li><li>Mapping reveals cultural and economic hubs</li><li>Patterns show strategic defense against threats</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Mapping Texican land grants helps visualize how settlements were distributed and how geography influenced community development and defense. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Locate Stephen F. Austin’s colony on a map and identify nearby rivers and trails.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Use a map to identify why certain areas were chosen for settlement.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring geographic factors like water access and terrain in settlement choices.</p></div></div>",
