    "id": "slide20",
    "eyebrow": "Identifying Characteristics",
    "num": "20",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">20</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Identifying Characteristics</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Key Traits Defining Texican Identity</h2><ul><li>Cultural hybridity blending Mexican and Anglo elements</li><li>Frontier resilience and adaptability</li><li>Political engagement in Texas independence</li><li>Strong community ties through missions and settlements</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican identity is marked by cultural blending, frontier lifestyle, political activism, and community cohesion, distinguishing them within Texas history. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A Texican leader balancing Mexican heritage with revolutionary ideals exemplifies this identity.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> List traits that make Texicans distinct from other Texas settlers.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Reducing Texican identity to a single cultural or political aspect.</p></div></div>",
