    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">26</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texican Lifestyle</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Daily Life on the Texican Frontier</h2><ul><li>Texicans lived in rural, often isolated communities</li><li>Economy based on farming, ranching, and trade</li><li>Homes were simple, built from local materials</li><li>Community events and church played central roles</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican daily life was shaped by frontier conditions, with families relying on agriculture and livestock. Social life centered around community gatherings and religious practices, reflecting Mexican cultural influences. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A typical Texican family might cultivate corn and raise cattle, attending church on Sundays and participating in local festivals.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Describe how frontier conditions influenced Texican economic and social activities.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overestimating urban development or infrastructure in early Texican settlements.</p></div></div>",
