    "num": "27",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">27</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Interactions</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Relations with Native American Tribes</h2><ul><li>Texicans had complex relationships with local tribes</li><li>Interactions ranged from trade to conflict</li><li>Native tribes influenced Texican defense and diplomacy</li><li>Some Texicans adopted Native customs and alliances</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans navigated a frontier shared with Native American tribes, leading to varied interactions. While conflicts occurred, trade and alliances were also common, impacting Texican survival and culture. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican settlers traded livestock and goods with tribes like the Comanche, sometimes forming alliances against common enemies.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Explain how Texican-Native American relations affected settlement security and culture.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing Native American relations as solely hostile or ignoring their diplomatic complexity.</p></div></div>",
