    "num": "28",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">28</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Identity</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Blending Mexican and Anglo Cultures in Texican Society</h2><ul><li>Texicans combined Mexican traditions with Anglo settler influences</li><li>Language, religion, and customs reflected this blend</li><li>Cultural tensions sometimes arose over governance and law</li><li>This blend shaped a unique Texican identity</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican culture was a fusion of Mexican heritage and Anglo-American settler customs, creating a distinct identity that influenced social norms, language use, and political attitudes. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican communities celebrated Catholic holidays while adopting Anglo-style town meetings for local governance.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify examples of cultural blending and tensions within Texican society.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texican culture was purely Mexican or purely Anglo without recognizing the hybrid nature.</p></div></div>",
