    "num": "29",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">29</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Historical Role</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texicans in the Texas Revolution</h2><ul><li>Texicans played key roles in political and military actions</li><li>They sought independence from Mexican central government</li><li>Texican leaders drafted and signed the Texas Declaration of Independence</li><li>Their actions led to the creation of the Republic of Texas</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans were central actors in the Texas Revolution, advocating for self-governance and participating in battles that led to Texas’ independence from Mexico. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican figures like Sam Houston led military campaigns culminating in the victory at San Jacinto.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Explain the motivations and contributions of Texicans during the revolution.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Attributing the revolution solely to Anglo settlers, ignoring Texican involvement.</p></div></div>",
