    "eyebrow": "Primary Source Analysis",
    "num": "30",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">30</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Source Analysis</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Examining the Texas Declaration of Independence</h2><ul><li>Document drafted and signed by Texican leaders in 1836</li><li>Outlined grievances against Mexican government</li><li>Asserted Texican right to self-governance</li><li>Reflects Texican political and cultural concerns</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Texas Declaration of Independence is a primary source revealing Texican perspectives on Mexican rule and their justification for revolution. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The declaration cites issues like lack of representation and violation of rights, echoing Texican demands for autonomy.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify key grievances in the declaration that reflect Texican interests.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Reading the declaration as a purely Anglo document without Texican influence.</p></div></div>",
